################################################################
# Setup a Media Server to stream from a cloud service provider #
################################################################

############
# The Plan #
############
#
# Stream Media to Plex (or Emby) from a Cloud Service Provider, such as Google Drive. 
# Media organised via Sonarr, Radarr and Sabnzbd Dockers.
# Rclone to Upload Media to Cloud Service Provider.
# Rclone will be used for mounts, and tpslimit flag to prevent api bans.
# Encrypt Media via Rclone Crypt.
#
# Usenet ------> Sabnzbd ------> Sonarr/Radarr ------> Rclone Crypt ------> Google Drive
# Google Drive -------> Rclone ------> Plex Playback
# Google Drive -------> Rclone ------> Sonnar Library Scanning
# Google Drive -------> Rclone ------> Radarr Library Scanning
# 
# 


################
# Requirements #
################
# Computer, VPS or Dedicated Server with Ubuntu 16.04 (Distribution Kernal).
# Cloud Storage Provider, such as Google Drive, Hubic, ACD (being disbanded) etc
